snippet.textDisplay:
Pheasant got it's posh characterization from being imported strictly for feudal lords or the king to hunt and eat. It would not have been on the menu for regular folks, because to get it you would have to poach them and that was punishable by death. This changed after the feudal system broke down, so I was happy they didn't rule it posh.
When I was a child, my dad hunted. We never considered game birds or other types of venison 'fancy', they were just food.

snippet.textDisplay:
Guys Esthechoc makes bold claims it can't back up. The Advertising Standards Authority in the UK actually told them to stop making the health/anti-ageing claims as the 'facts' aren't approved by the EU's food safety register, and they can't provide adequate evidence to uphold them. Nevertheless they continue to imply there are benefits absolutely everywhere they can, while 'the science' section of their website is curiously broken...


Just wanted to let you know. Faux science is rampant online & in the media and it can be really hard to notice. But I think if you look into it, paying £30 for something that might work, but also might harm you, or do nothing at all that apparently also tastes bad is... silly.

Love the episode!
